values.name: hsl
values.comment:
HSL color function.

Which takes the parameters `h`, `s` and `l`.
Where `h` is max 360 (degrees), `s` max 100 (pct) and `l` max 100 (pct) as well.
So given the CSS statement `hsl(232.7, 20.3%, 12%)`, you'd say:

    hsl 232.7 20.3 12

values.name: rgb
values.comment:
RGB color function.

Which takes the parameters `r`, `g` and `b`.
Each of which have a maximum value of 255.
Equivalent to the standard CSS rgb usage.

    rgb 255 255 255

values.name: chunk
values.comment:
Function for easier styling using classes.

    chunk
        Html.a
        [ "underline", "text-blue" ]
        [ href "" ]
        [ Html.text "" ]

Is the same as:

    Html.a
        [ class "underline text-blue", href "" ]
        [ Html.text "" ]
